Package: growthstandards
Title: Anthropometric Growth Standard Calculations
Version: 0.1.6
Authors@R: person("Ryan", "Hafen", email = "rhafen@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Convert anthropometric measurements to or from z-scores and centiles
    using the WHO and INTERGROWTH growth standards. The WHO standard are used
    for infants, children, and young adults. INTERGROWTH standards are
    provided for fetal and newborn (including very preterm) calculations.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://ki-tools.github.io/growthstandards/
LazyData: yes
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports:
    lattice,
    gamlss.dist,
    ggplot2,
    grid,
    dplyr
Suggests:
    testthat,
    covr,
    lintr,
    knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
BugReports: https://github.com/ki-tools/growthstandards/issues
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
